\begin{align*}
(a-3d) + (a-d) + (a+d) + (a+3d) &= 360^{\circ}\\
4a &= 360^{\circ}\\
a &= 90^{\circ} \end{align*}
Since the largest angle is $129^{\circ}$, we have:
\begin{align*}
a+3d &= 129^{\circ}\\
90^{\circ}+3d &= 129^{\circ}\\
3d &= 39^{\circ}\\
d &= 13^{\circ} \end{align*}
Therefore, the measure of the second largest angle is $a-d = 90^{\circ}-13^{\circ} = \boxed{77^{\circ}}$.
